## Key Concepts
- **Per-tenant QoS**: cgroups v2 for resource isolation combined with tc (HTB, fq_codel) for bandwidth shaping and flow scheduling
- **XDP/BPF load balancing**: Kernel-bypass packet processing with per-tenant queue isolation to eliminate contention
- **Hardware affinity**: IRQ pinning and NUMA-aware CPU/memory topology to reduce latency introduced by cross-socket communication
- **Staged testing**: Incremental load validation with defined rollback criteria ensures safe production deployment

## Code Example
```c
struct bpf_map_def SEC("maps") tenant_queue_map = {
    .type = BPF_MAP_TYPE_HASH,
    .key_size = sizeof(__u32),
    .value_size = sizeof(struct tenant_queue),
    .max_entries = 1024,
};

struct tenant_queue {
    __u32 rx_packets;
    __u32 rx_drops;
    __u64 last_tstamp;
};

SEC("xdp") int redirect_per_tenant(struct xdp_md *ctx) {
    void *data = (void *)(long)ctx->data;
    void *data_end = (void *)(long)ctx->data_end;
    struct ethhdr *eth = data;

    if (data + sizeof(*eth) > data_end)
        return XDP_PASS;

    __u32 tenant_id = get_tenant_id(eth);
    struct tenant_queue *q = bpf_map_lookup_elem(&tenant_queue_map, &tenant_id);

    if (q)
        q->rx_packets++;

    return XDP_REDIRECT;
}
```

